725904f-a.title: Queens: 150th Street - 150th Avenue
725904f-a.text:
150th Street, at the S.W. corner of 150th Ave., showing the
Federicks house;owned by William Dull in 1913.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725903f-b.title: Queens: 150th Street - 150th Avenue
725903f-b.text:
150th Street, at the N.W. corner of One Hundred Fiftieth Ave.,
showing in a set of three views the J.C. Reimels farmhouse of 1913.
James Francis was the owner in 1873, followed by his son, and then
the present J.C. Mrs. Reimels had it in 1922 and William Dull
in 1934. Another owner was B. Headerson from 1860 to 1873.
1922.
Views 1,2 and 3.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
